```c
// Data structure for an artificial neuron
typedef struct {
  int num_inputs;    // Number of inputs to the neuron
  double *weights;   // Array of weights for each input
  double bias;       // Bias term for the neuron
  double output;     // Output value of the neuron
  double delta;      // Delta value of the neuron (for backpropagation)
} Neuron;

// Data structure for a single layer of an MLP
typedef struct {
  int num_neurons;   // Number of neurons in the layer
  Neuron *neurons;   // Array of neurons in the layer
} Layer;

// Data structure for an MLP with an arbitrary number of layers
typedef struct {
  int num_layers;    // Number of layers in the MLP
  Layer *layers;     // Array of layers in the MLP
} MLP;
```
The `Neuron` struct contains the number of inputs to the neuron, an array of weights for each input, the bias term for the neuron, the output value of the neuron, and the delta value of the neuron (for backpropagation).

The `Layer` struct contains the number of neurons in the layer and an array of neurons in the layer.

The `MLP` struct contains the number of layers in the MLP and an array of layers in the MLP.

Note that these data structures are designed to store the model parameters and intermediate values for a forward pass of the MLP, but do not include any functions or algorithms for computing the forward pass or backpropagation. These will need to be implemented separately.

