Here is an example of how to configure the Kafka-flux extension for real-time streaming ingestion from Kafka in Druid:
```yaml
{
  "dataSources": [
    {
      "spec": {
        "dataSchema": {
          "dataSource": "example-data",
          "granularitySpec": {
            "type": "uniform",
            "segmentGranularity": "HOUR",
            "queryGranularity": "NONE",
            "intervals": ["2018-01-01T00:00:00.000Z/2018-01-02T00:00:00.000Z"]
          },
          "parser": {
            "type": "string",
            "parseSpec": {
              "timestampSpec": {
                "column": "timestamp",
                "format": "auto"
              },
              "dimensionsSpec": {
                "dimensions": ["userId", "pageId", "eventType", "userAgent"],
                "dimensionExclusions": [],
                "spatialDimensions": []
              },
              "format": "json"
            }
          },
          "metricsSpec": [
            {
              "name": "count",
              "type": "count"
            }
          ],
          "tuningConfig": {
            "type": "kafka-flux",
            "maxRowsPerSegment": 5000000,
            "windowPeriod": "PT30S",
            "basePersistDirectory": "/var/druid/segments",
            "consumer": {
              "bootstrap.servers": "kafka-broker1:9092,kafka-broker2:9092",
              "group.id": "druid-kafka-ingest",
              "enable.auto.commit": false
            },
            "parallelismHint": 1
          }
        },
        "tuningConfig": {
          "type": "kafka-flux",
          "maxRowsInMemory": 100000,
          "intermediatePersistPeriod": "PT10M",
          "windowPeriod": "PT30S"
        }
      },
      "properties": {
        "topicPattern": "example-topic.*",
        "consumerProps.override.auto.offset.reset": "earliest",
        "consumerProps.override.max.partition.fetch.bytes": "1048576"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```
This example configuration file specifies a Druid data source that ingests data from Kafka using the Kafka-flux indexing service. Some key configuration properties include:

* `tuningConfig.type`: Set to `"kafka-flux"` to use the Kafka-flux indexing service.
* `maxRowsPerSegment`: The maximum number of rows to include in each Druid segment.
* `windowPeriod`: The amount of time to buffer incoming data before flushing to disk.
* `consumer.bootstrap.servers`: The list of Kafka brokers to connect to.
* `topicPattern`: A regular expression pattern to match the Kafka topics to ingest.
* `consumerProps.override.auto.offset.reset`: The strategy for resetting the Kafka consumer's offset when there is no initial offset or the current offset is out of range.
* `consumerProps.override.max.partition.fetch.bytes`: The maximum number of bytes to fetch from a single Kafka partition in one request.

